The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease dated 17 Apr 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 1302, of which 1236 are confirmed and 66 are probable. In total, there were 843 deaths (777 confirmed and 66 probable) and 380 people healed.
- 325 suspected cases are under investigation.
- 12 new confirmed cases, including 5 in Katwa, 3 in Mandima, 2 in Vuhovi, 1 in Kalunguta and 1 in Beni.
- 10 new confirmed case deaths, including 7 community deaths, including 3 in Mandima, 2 in Vuhovi, 1 in Katwa, and 1 in Kalunguta; 3 deaths at ETCs, 2 in Butembo and 1 in Katwa.
- 1 new recovered person discharged from the ETC of Komanda.

