Excerpts:
- DRC reaches 100 000 people vaccinated against Ebola in North Kivu and Ituri.
- The significant increase in new cases confirmed in recent weeks, particularly in active households in Butembo and Katwa, is partly explained by the temporary cessation of vaccination activities in March [2019] following the rise in violence against the teams of the response. Because of the problems of violence and safety, 45 vaccination rings could not be opened around confirmed cases.

